For anyone having trouble, I've decided to write a little tutorial on how to install it (as I myself had a time figuring out how to do it).

1. Download the torrent.
2. Navigate to the folder where it is saved, and double-click it. Next, open the folder called CD1.
2. Unrar the first RAR file in the folder using WinRAR, available at www.rarlabs.com. Repeat this step for the first RAR files in the CD2 and CD3 directories as well.
3. Next you'll need a program to mount the image files, I used IsoBuster (http://thepiratebay.org/tor/3606269/IsoBuster_Pro_v1.9.1.1_.Final.Cracked-GMSi%5BSEED). Open and extract each of the .bin files you just unRARed to a folder you'll be able to find later. There should be 3 .bin files, one from each of the CD1, CD2, and CD3 directories.
4. Once you've extracted all the files using IsoBuster (or similar program), go there. In each of the folders from the 3 separate image files you'll find another RAR file. UnRAR all files in these packages to the same directory, but make sure to put them in the folder where the original image file was extracted. (For example, if you extracted the .bin file in the CD1 folder to C:\Program Files\Microsoft Games\AoE3\AoE III Disc 1, then unpack all the files contained within the 3 separate RAR packages to the same folder).
5. Once done, run the setup.exe file.
6. During the installation process, you will be asked for a serial code. Use the following serial: DXR32-X44M7-CYTCX-P6H6P-97CPG
7. Once the game finishes installing, go into the Crack folder contained within the initial image file, and copy the file called age3.exe into the directory where Age of Empires III was installed (typically C:\Program Files\Microsoft Games\Age of Empires III). It will ask you if you want to overwrite the file with the same name that already exists, click Yes.
Ta-da, you're done! Enjoy playing AoE3 and thanks to whoever provided this amazing torrent!

For those having trouble install anything here is a step by step instruction on how to install this game:

1.Get this torrent first and finish downloading, seeding helps for those of you who don't want to...
2.Download and Install DAEMON lite tools, the newest one
3.Open the CD1 folder and make sure to have winRAR, if not download and install winRAR, google it like DAEMON lite tools.
4.Open the first winRAR file and then extract the one file named BIN to the desktop or where you can locate it easily the file named CUE with go along with it.
5.Then on the icon of the DAEMON lite tools right-click and where Virtual CD/DVD ROM is follow the arrow until it says mount image.
6.Locate the file that you extracted and mount it and install the first CD, follow this step until your done with CD3.
7.Now the file called REloaded right click and highlight "Open With" choose Notepad to get the CD key
8.Now mount CD1 again and click on the start>computer
9.When that opens right click on the CD drive with the age of empires logo and choose "Explore".
10.The file Crack should be there drag and drop it to the desktop or any where you can easily locate it and save it there.
11.Now open the file Crack and right click copy and open start>computer and go to C:\Program Files\Microsoft Games\Age of Empires III and copy, and overwrite the old one and now your are 90% complete.
12.Now go to www.gamecopyworld.com and navigate to locate a file called "Age Of Empires 3 v1.12[English/German] No-CD/Fixed EXE".
13.Now go to the Age of Empires Offical site and download the new v1.12 offical patch and download and install it.
14.Now unRAR the file you download from www.gamecopyworld.com and do the same thing as step 10-11.
15.Finally you can run and enjoy the game with out any need for CDs or slowdowns due to lack of reading a disc :)!!! What you do is once you're done downloading, you go to the AOE III folder and open the CD1 folder...in it you'll find many .rar files, double click on any one of them and WinRAR will open (if you have it installed on your PC) then in the WinRAR Window you'll find a rdl-aoea.bin folder.
What you do is you click on the "Up one level" button on the top right corner next to the folder name and select all the .rar files and extract to a folder on your desktop or wherever.
Do the same for CD2 and CD3 folder.

After you've done that, go to the taskbar and find the Daemon Tools icon on it, right click> Virtual CD/DVD-rom> Device 0:...> Mount Image.
Now you're going to mount the image that you extracted, use the autorun feature...install and play :D

Hope this helped
oh yeah, and when it asks to put CD2 and CD3 you just mount over the image that was recently mounted...you don't have to unmount any images.

Guide-
Part 1
Things you'll need-
1.Some torrent program to download file ( i used bitorrent)
2.Winrar( to unrar the files that i tell you to unrar)
3.Daemon Tool (to mount the cue files)
Steps-
1.Download torrent
2.Once its done go to your desktop (or wherever you downloaded it to) and open it and go to CD1 folder.
2A.In the CD1 folder you'll see A LOT of files but don't get scared XD. Look for a file called rld_aoea BUT make sure that the file your looking at says RAR file but doesn't have a rar image on it. Click it and use winrar to open it. Once its opened drag the 2 files you see in it
rld-aoea.bin rld-aoea.cue
3.Now go to your desktop lets say and make some folder with any name and drag those 2 files into it.
4. Now repeat step 2A and 3 for CD2 and CD3 but instead of rld_aoea it'll say aoeb then aoeb. 
NOTE-After you have opened the first rar file in CD1 wiht no name when you look in CD2 and 3 you'll see a similar file with the same icon that shows a white box outside of the rar image.
5. Ok now should should have 6 files in that folder you made. Those files should be
rld-aoea.bin rld-aoea.cue rld-aoeb.bin rld-aoeb.cue rld-aoec.bin rld-aoec.cue
If you have all those files in your folder good..
6. Now all that is left is some simple installing.
Go to your Daemon tools control panel and (if you have DAEMON Tools Lite) there should be a small orange ball with a arrow pointing up click that and click Device0: [F:] NOTE- It may be different depending on your system. Now a little window should come up saying "Select Image File" now navigate your way to that folder where you dropped the 6 files and click the one that says
rld-aoea.cueand it should mount it.

Part 2
7. Ok now the installation window for Age of Empires should come and ask you for a code before you can install. Pick any on of these
I reccomend-
DXR32-X44M7-CYTCX-P6H6P-97CPG 
These might work-
WPXD8-7XYFR-4828Q-FV88X-7DGDJ
JKK3F-J8CK9-Q33PF-W88FY-MGBBT
After that it'll start installing and your good til..
7A- IT ASKS YOU FOR CD2!! Don't freak out ok
Just go to Daemon Tools again and this time mount rld-aoeb.cue and it should continue installing.
7B- Near the end it'll ask you to put in CD3 so this time mount the last one rld-aoec.cue
There you go, where almost done, when it finishes it'll ask you to restart your computer do it. NOTE-It MIGHT ask you to put in CD1 again after installation finishes this isn't a bug but a DirectX update for the game and more. So just mount rld-aoea.cue again.

Part 3

Ok. This torrent works. And for the complete noobs the installation instructions:-

3. Ignore the cue file, its useless and mount the bin file using daemon tools. for that, you see the task bar on the bottom right, right click on the red and white lightning symbol-> virtual cd/dvd rom -> device X is empty->mount image.
You need to select 'all files' in the pop up window to use the bin file.
4. Do for the remaining two cds appropriately
5. Use the CD key, it works. Make sure you are typing all in capitals, and be careful not to add typos and mistakes. Still not working, then google for other cd keys.
6. follow the instructions of installation.
7. After installation, use crack on the cd1 to replace the original AOE3 icon in its folder you decided during installation.

Age of empires 3 is well, fantastic. I was a big fan of AOE 2 and it was the first RTS i played.

For those having intel grahics card of g33/g31 crap, turn off lightning effects in options-> graphics. that should make it playable.
